<topic id="sql-transformation">
  <title>SQL Transformation</title>
  <!--Proofed-->
  <body>
    <p>To create an <uicontrol>SQL transformation</uicontrol> scenario, use one of the following
        methods:<ul id="ul_mww_l13_br">
        <li>Go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Show View</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> and select <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"
              id="image_ijb_5vv_sr"/>Transformation Scenarios</uicontrol> to display this view.
          Click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select <uicontrol>SQL
            transformation</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png" id="image_jlg_5vv_sr"
            />Configure Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/shortcut_ctrl_shift_c"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/alt_shift_tc_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol> toolbar or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol> Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>SQL transformation</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>Use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/ApplyStyleSheet16.png" id="image_utw_2xs_1r"
            />Apply Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/ctrl-shift-t-shortcut"
              product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
              conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/alt_shift_tt_shortcut"
              product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
            <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol> toolbar or the <menucascade
            product="author developer editor">
            <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol> Transformation</uicontrol>
          </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
            >XML</uicontrol> menu. Then click the <uicontrol>New</uicontrol> button and select
            <uicontrol>SQL transformation</uicontrol>.<note
            conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/note-001"/>All three methods open the
            <uicontrol>New Scenario</uicontrol> dialog box. This dialog box allows you to configure
          the following options that control the transformation:<ul>
            <li><uicontrol>Name</uicontrol> - The unique name of the SQL transformation
              scenario.</li>
            <li><ph product="author developer editor"><uicontrol>Storage</uicontrol> - Allows you to
                select one of the following storage options:</ph><ul
                product="author developer editor">
                <li conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/global-options-li"/>
                <li conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/project-options-li"/>
              </ul></li>
            <li><uicontrol>SQL URL</uicontrol> - Allows you to specify the URL of the SQL script.
              You can use the following browsing buttons to enter value in this field:<dl
                conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/browsing-buttons">
                <dlentry>
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl></li>
            <li><uicontrol>Connection</uicontrol> - Allows you to select a connection from a
              drop-down list. To configure a connection, use the <uicontrol><image
                  href="../img/OptionsShortcut16.gif" id="image_lhk_jnt_tr"/>Advanced
                options</uicontrol> button to open the <xref
                href="preferences-data-sources.dita#preferences-data-sources">data source
                preferences page</xref>.</li>
            <li><uicontrol>Parameters</uicontrol> - Allows you to configure the parameters of the
              transformation.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
</topic>
